Description:

cs_nakatomi is a Die Hard map for the very popular, Counterstrike:Source. It is based on the first Die Hard movie, starring Bruce Willis. The map itself is a hostage rescue map, consisting of three levels; rooftop (CT spawn), office/contsruction floor and the nakatomi skylobby (T spawn)

Features:

- A variety of ways to navigate the map (ventilation system, elevator shaft, stairwell etc.)
- 16 player support
- An amazing die hard experience

This is just an edit of my fy_mountain_home_mansion map.  I added some rain, cool effects, sounds, and made it a hostage rescue with different spawn zones.  The CT team gets two spawn areas, front and back of the house and T team gets basement and fireplace room to start.  And yes this is seriously version 100; from start to finish, I changed and ran this map about 100 times to perfect it.

**EDIT IMPORTANT NOTICE**  I had to update this map due to an error caused by an invalid ct spawn point which at maximum occupancy will leave one player stuck into the ground!  If you downloaded this map before August 29, delete it and download it again!***********

**IMPORTANT NOTICE NUMBER 2**  I have yet again updated this map on August 29, any user who downloaded on or before that date should delete the map and redownload!  It wasn't a big deal, just a simple texture misplacement!  I removed it and have fixed it now!

CS_MOTEL_NIGHT by Hightower (released February 2009)

"The mapper did not release one but four versions of his map. It is available as a hostage or defuse map and both are available in day or night versions. With an ugly map it's making no sense, but as the map is pretty good, very realistic and is based on a rarely seen location, these little variations around a common theme are a nice idea... If you're looking for large urban chaotic combat map, well, look somewhere else. If you're looking for an infiltration map where danger is behind every door, check this one!" - from map review at Netday.be

Here is a nighttime version of map. Daytime version you can download here.

See also both Bomb/Defuse versions of map by original author: de_motel and de_motel_night.

NOTE: Here you can also download the hand-tuned NAV-file (Navigation Mesh for Bots) for this map, because the one included in original .bsp-file simple auto-generated NAV is NOT FULLY playable!

Great Thanks and Good Luck!

_sText:
cs_motel88.txt Read Me
-------------------------

CONTENTS

 1.Whats in the .zip file?
 2.Installation
 3.Description
 4.Notes/errors
 5.Author and acknowledgments
-------------------------

1.Whats in the .zip file

2x Folders with:
 1x ReadMe.txt(obviously:)
 ---1x cs_motel88.bsp map file
 ---1x cs_motel88.nav map file
 ---6x in-game Screen shots

-------------------------

2.Installation:
  
      Just place or extract the cstrike folder into your Counter-Strike: Source directory. For example place the files in these directories: "C:\Program Files/Steam/steamapps/"your user name"/counter-strike source/cstrike/maps/" 

!!!!P.S. Open this "cstrike" folder, and then extract the contens inside of it, i,e; the "maps folder" into STEAMS original folder named "cstrike," other wise it will place this "cstrike folder" inside your "cstrike folder."!!!! 
-------------------------

3.Description:

   This is my first attempt at making a high rise map for Counter-Strike: Source. It was meant to be a Hostage Rescue map but the hosties won't make it all the way down to the lobby where the rescue zones. They get caught up on the stairs some how, I don't know why, and I don't know how to fix these problem yet. So, you can try and lead them out or just play it as a Deathmatch or Fight Yard I guess. The concept came to me as a hotel from another country(I'm from the U.S.A. BTW.) Its no place specific i,e; this motel/hotel doesn't exist or far as I know it doesn't(I've never been out of the U.S.A.) I just kind a pieced it all together a little at a time. Any ways, there is no LIGHTING as I can't get the lights to illuminate the bottom floors appropriately. So there is only the default engine lighting right now.    

-------------------------

4.Notes/errors:

 a.Lighting sucks and I apologize, but so do my lighting skills. =P 

 b.Brushes and textures are still not aligned and/or might be slightly out of place and size.

 c.This map has the standard CS:S load out with the VGUI buy screens.
 
 d.There are 8vs8 CT and T spawning's, so there is 16 spawns in all. And Bots do have      info_nodes.
 
 -------------------------

5.Author and Acknowledgments:

 + Map by: Chase"ArrogantOrange"Miller

 + Tutorials and training provided by: 3kliksphilip You can find him and his tutorials on          YouTube at http://www.youtube.com/user/3kliksphilip

 + A big thanx to Valve(obviously)for their great games and the SOURCE SDK(and other versions) 

 + and as always to the Mapers/Moders like you who give me a reason to keep chugging a way at    this designing dream...thingy, I have =)

  Thanx FBSBanana.  
  
    Sincerely,
  Arrogant Orange
-------------------------
-------------------------
-------------------------

I tried to approach gameplay from a unique angle, one that revolves around pseudo-realistic improvation to assure survival during firefights [as opposed to having totally straight forward objectives and routes like most official maps]

Remastered and more detailed cs-version of de_MkZk_Proto_v1.

Teams spawn outside, the time it takes to enter the house and reach the bombspots or walk around the area is balanced for both teams.
Attic and Basement are A and B.

Features a camera-monitor system and a tactical easteregg, there is a hint for it somewhere in the map.

Changes:

  • One more room to the top apartment +2nd balcony.
  • Put an ivy-trellis on the main building to have another access to the 2nd floor from outside.
  • Added a small shed + pool to the garden.
  • Created two entirely new areas, one backyard and added rooms and floors to another building to connect the garden with both streets to increase tactic-options.
  • And obviously added many props and sounds, changed some small things in several areas and made the whole thing more realistic.

Further versions are coming soon.

If there are things to fix or any ideas to improve it let me know in the comments.

Cs_mi_port by max42

Extended and reworked version of de_ports so that it is now a hostage map. Full of new rooms and added features - 

Take a boat around the bay
Get stuck in jail
Watch the action on one of the 3 cameras on the map
Go to the top of the crane
Find the hidden awp and grenades in both spawns
climb the hidden ladder onto the hill - by ct spawn
Tanks near one of the old bomb sites now explode when you destroy a box

New rooms - Security Room, Restrooms, Storage rooms, generator room

Hundreds of changes made, all areas of the maps can be got at one way or another - by climbing to them using hidden 
ladders, using the drainpipes, blowing up gates.

2 of the warehouses have been completly re-built

3 hidden weapon disposits - one at ct spawn, one at t spawn and one near the hostages in the smaller building

20 player spawn points, map starts to lag if more than 8 players are on there

And of course - rescue the hostages!


Credits

max42 - mapper
ickle - researcher
